---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Norse Mythology — Viking Vocabulary for Big Scores"
  description="Norse mythology words valid in Scrabble. VALKYRIE (18pts), VIKING (14pts), RUNE (4pts). Which mythological terms are legal and which aren't?"
  keywords="scrabble norse mythology words, viking scrabble points, valkyrie scrabble, rune scrabble, norse words scrabble, mythology vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Norse Mythology — Viking Vocabulary for Big Scores","description":"Norse mythology words valid in Scrabble. VALKYRIE (18pts), VIKING (14pts), RUNE (4pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-norse"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is VALKYRIE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! VALKYRIE scores 18 points (V=4, A=1, L=1, K=5, Y=4, R=1, I=1, E=1). As an 8-letter word, it's a bingo candidate worth 18 + 50 bonus = 68 points if you use all tiles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play VIKING in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. VIKING scores 14 points (V=4, I=1, K=5, I=1, N=1, G=2). It's valid in both SOWPODS and TWL dictionaries as a common English word derived from Norse culture."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MJOLNIR valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. MJOLNIR is not in any official Scrabble dictionary. It remains a proper noun (Thor's hammer). However, words like RUNE (4pts), VIKING (14pts), and VALKYRIE (18pts) are all valid."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Norse Mythology — Viking Vocabulary for Big Scores</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Norse mythology has gifted English with powerful words — some valid in Scrabble, others frustratingly not. VALKYRIE and VIKING deliver massive points, while iconic terms like MJOLNIR and ODIN remain off-limits as proper nouns. Here's your guide to what's legal and what's legendary.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">VALKYRIE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">VIKING</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RUNE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">❌</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MJOLNIR</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Valid Norse-Origin Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">VALKYRIE — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">V=4, A=1, L=1, K=5, Y=4, R=1, I=1, E=1 · 8 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A chooser of the slain in Norse mythology. VALKYRIE is an 8-letter bingo candidate scoring 18 base points plus the 50-point bonus for using all tiles — a devastating 68-point play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ VIKING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · V=4, I=1, K=5, I=1, N=1, G=2 · Norse raider</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✨ RUNE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">4 pts · R=1, U=1, N=1, E=1 · Ancient letter</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🐺 FENRIR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · F=4, E=1, N=1, R=1, I=1, R=1 · Giant wolf (SOWPODS)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌊 FJORD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · F=4, J=8, O=1, R=1, D=2 · Coastal inlet</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Invalid Norse Words (Proper Nouns)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">❌ MJOLNIR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Proper noun — Thor's hammer. Not in any dictionary.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">❌ ODIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Proper noun — chief god. Not valid.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">❌ ASGARD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Proper noun — realm of gods. Not valid.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">❌ RAGNAROK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Proper noun — end of days. Not valid.</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Valid Norse-Derived Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BERSERK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RUNIC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SAGA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TROLL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SKALD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FJORD is the J-tile jackpot:</span> At 16 points (F=4, J=8, O=1, R=1, D=2), FJORD is one of the best 5-letter J words available. The J=8 alone makes it worthwhile.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Save VALKYRIE for the bingo:</span> At 8 letters, VALKYRIE naturally qualifies for the 50-point bonus. Hold V, K, and Y together — the remaining letters (A, L, R, I, E) are common draws.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">RUNE hooks into RUNES and RUNED:</span> Low-scoring alone at 4 points, but RUNE sets up parallel plays and hooks easily with S, D, or S for future turns.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Norse mythology words split into two camps: <span class="text-white font-medium">common nouns that entered English</span> (valid) and <span class="text-white font-medium">proper nouns</span> (invalid). VIKING, VALKYRIE, FJORD, and BERSERK are all legal because they became regular English words.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-vikings/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Vikings</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-japanese/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology Japanese</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-celtic/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology Celtic</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-egyptian/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology Egyptian</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-hindu/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology Hindu</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-greek/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Greek Mythology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-origin-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Origin Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any Norse word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
